---
/**
 * community-guidelines.astro
 * Community Guidelines for WorldBridger One
 *
 * Outlines expected behavior, battle etiquette, and
 * content standards for our creative community
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = "February 5, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title="Community Guidelines" description="WorldBridger One Community Guidelines - Rules for respectful creative expression">
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <h1>Community Guidelines</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p class="intro">
          WorldBridger One is a creative community where artists compete, collaborate, and grow together.
          These guidelines help us maintain a space that's competitive yet respectful, edgy yet inclusive.
        </p>
      </header>

      <nav class="legal-toc">
        <h2>Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#philosophy">Our Philosophy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#golden-rules">Golden Rules</a></li>
          <li><a href="#battle-etiquette">Battle Etiquette</a></li>
          <li><a href="#content-standards">Content Standards</a></li>
          <li><a href="#prohibited">Prohibited Content & Behavior</a></li>
          <li><a href="#youth-safety">Youth Safety</a></li>
          <li><a href="#reporting">Reporting & Moderation</a></li>
          <li><a href="#consequences">Consequences</a></li>
          <li><a href="#appeals">Appeals Process</a></li>
          <li><a href="#community-values">Community Values</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <article class="legal-content">

        <section id="philosophy">
          <h2>1. Our Philosophy</h2>
          <p>
            WorldBridger One sits at the intersection of hip-hop culture, blockchain technology,
            and youth empowerment. We believe in:
          </p>
          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>Core Beliefs</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Creative Freedom:</strong> Artists should express themselves boldly</li>
              <li><strong>Respectful Competition:</strong> Battles are about skill, not personal attacks</li>
              <li><strong>Inclusive Community:</strong> Everyone deserves a seat at the cipher</li>
              <li><strong>Youth First:</strong> Protecting and empowering young creators</li>
              <li><strong>Open Source Spirit:</strong> Sharing knowledge lifts everyone up</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>
            These guidelines aren't about limiting creativity—they're about creating an environment
            where ALL artists can thrive and compete fairly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="golden-rules">
          <h2>2. Golden Rules</h2>
          <p>If you remember nothing else, remember these:</p>
          <div class="rules-grid">
            <div class="rule-card">
              <span class="rule-number">1</span>
              <h3>Attack the Bars, Not the Person</h3>
              <p>In battles, target someone's rhymes, flow, or delivery—never their identity, family, or personal struggles.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-card">
              <span class="rule-number">2</span>
              <h3>Lift While You Climb</h3>
              <p>Share knowledge, give feedback, help newcomers. The community grows when we support each other.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-card">
              <span class="rule-number">3</span>
              <h3>Keep It Real, Keep It Legal</h3>
              <p>Be authentic in your art, but don't cross lines into illegal activity, threats, or harm.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-card">
              <span class="rule-number">4</span>
              <h3>Protect the Youth</h3>
              <p>Many of our users are young artists. Keep adult content clearly labeled and age-gated.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="battle-etiquette">
          <h2>3. Battle Etiquette</h2>
          <p>
            Rap battles are competitive by nature. We embrace the tradition of battle rap while
            maintaining standards that keep competitions fair and enjoyable.
          </p>

          <h3>3.1 What's Encouraged</h3>
          <ul class="green-list">
            <li>Clever wordplay and punchlines</li>
            <li>Creative disses about someone's rapping ability</li>
            <li>Flipping your opponent's bars against them</li>
            <li>Confident delivery and stage presence</li>
            <li>Referencing public personas and battle personas</li>
            <li>Humor and wit, even when it's cutting</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.2 What's Allowed (With Caution)</h3>
          <ul class="yellow-list">
            <li>Mature language (in 18+ battles only)</li>
            <li>Edgy humor that pushes boundaries</li>
            <li>Competitive trash talk</li>
            <li>References to public information about opponents</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.3 What's Never Acceptable</h3>
          <ul class="red-list">
            <li>Threats of real violence or harm</li>
            <li>Doxxing (revealing private information)</li>
            <li>Racist, sexist, homophobic, or ableist slurs used maliciously</li>
            <li>Attacks on someone's children or family members</li>
            <li>References to someone's mental health struggles or trauma</li>
            <li>Sexual content involving minors (instant permanent ban)</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="example-box">
            <h4>Examples</h4>
            <div class="example good">
              <span class="label">Acceptable:</span>
              <p>"Your flow's so slow, even dial-up would be embarrassed"</p>
            </div>
            <div class="example bad">
              <span class="label">Not Acceptable:</span>
              <p>Personal attacks on someone's real-life struggles, family, or identity</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="content-standards">
          <h2>4. Content Standards</h2>

          <h3>4.1 Music & Beats</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Original Work:</strong> Only upload content you created or have rights to use</li>
            <li><strong>Samples:</strong> Ensure you have clearance for any samples used</li>
            <li><strong>Collaborations:</strong> Credit all collaborators appropriately</li>
            <li><strong>Quality:</strong> Maintain reasonable audio quality standards</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>4.2 Profile Content</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Avatars:</strong> No explicit imagery in avatars (visible to all users)</li>
            <li><strong>Bios:</strong> Keep bios creative but appropriate for general audiences</li>
            <li><strong>Links:</strong> External links must comply with our guidelines</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>4.3 NFT Content</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> Only mint NFTs for content you own</li>
            <li><strong>Representation:</strong> Don't mislead buyers about NFT benefits or rarity</li>
            <li><strong>Permanence:</strong> Remember that blockchain content is permanent</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>4.4 Age-Gated Content</h3>
          <p>
            Content containing explicit language, mature themes, or adult content must be:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Clearly marked with appropriate content warnings</li>
            <li>Submitted to 18+ battles only</li>
            <li>Not accessible to users who haven't verified age 18+</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="prohibited">
          <h2>5. Prohibited Content & Behavior</h2>
          <p>The following will result in immediate action:</p>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h3>Zero Tolerance</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>CSAM:</strong> Any sexual content involving minors</li>
              <li><strong>Terrorism:</strong> Content promoting terrorist activities</li>
              <li><strong>Targeted Harassment:</strong> Coordinated attacks on individuals</li>
              <li><strong>Doxxing:</strong> Sharing private personal information</li>
              <li><strong>Credible Threats:</strong> Real threats of violence</li>
              <li><strong>Scams:</strong> Fraudulent schemes targeting community members</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3>5.1 Harassment</h3>
          <p>
            There's a difference between battle rap disses and harassment.
            Harassment includes:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Repeated unwanted contact after being asked to stop</li>
            <li>Following someone across platforms to attack them</li>
            <li>Encouraging others to target an individual</li>
            <li>Creating accounts to evade blocks</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>5.2 Hate Speech</h3>
          <p>
            We distinguish between edgy battle content and genuine hate speech.
            Hate speech includes:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Content promoting violence against protected groups</li>
            <li>Dehumanizing language targeting identity groups</li>
            <li>Symbols or imagery associated with hate movements</li>
            <li>Denial of historical atrocities</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>5.3 Illegal Activity</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Drug trafficking or illegal weapons sales</li>
            <li>Money laundering schemes</li>
            <li>Copyright infringement</li>
            <li>Hacking or unauthorized access</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>5.4 Platform Manipulation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Vote manipulation in battles</li>
            <li>Fake accounts or bot activity</li>
            <li>Wash trading NFTs</li>
            <li>XP farming through exploits</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="youth-safety">
          <h2>6. Youth Safety</h2>
          <p>
            WorldBridger One is committed to being a safe space for young artists.
            We take youth safety seriously.
          </p>

          <h3>6.1 Age Verification</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Financial features (NFT trading, token transfers) require age 18+</li>
            <li>18+ battles require age verification</li>
            <li>Users under 13 should have parental supervision</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>6.2 Protecting Young Users</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Never ask users for their age in ways meant to identify minors for targeting</li>
            <li>Don't request private contact with users who appear to be minors</li>
            <li>Report any suspicious behavior toward young users immediately</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>6.3 Adult User Responsibilities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Be mindful that young artists are present in the community</li>
            <li>Keep explicit content in age-appropriate spaces</li>
            <li>Be a positive mentor, not a predator</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="reporting">
          <h2>7. Reporting & Moderation</h2>

          <h3>7.1 How to Report</h3>
          <p>If you see content or behavior that violates these guidelines:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>In-App:</strong> Use the report button on any content or profile</li>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:safety@worldbridger.one">safety@worldbridger.one</a></li>
            <li><strong>Discord:</strong> Contact a moderator in #report-issues</li>
            <li><strong>Urgent:</strong> For immediate safety concerns, also contact local authorities</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>7.2 What Happens When You Report</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Your report is received and logged</li>
            <li>Our moderation team reviews the content</li>
            <li>We take appropriate action based on our guidelines</li>
            <li>You may receive a follow-up about the outcome (when appropriate)</li>
          </ol>

          <h3>7.3 Our Moderation Approach</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Context Matters:</strong> We consider context in battle rap vs. general content</li>
            <li><strong>Proportional Response:</strong> Actions match the severity of violations</li>
            <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> We apply rules fairly across all users</li>
            <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> We explain our decisions when possible</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>7.4 Community Moderation</h3>
          <p>
            As a decentralized platform, we also empower community moderation:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Token holders can vote on governance proposals</li>
            <li>Community members can become verified moderators</li>
            <li>Battle judges help enforce battle-specific rules</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="consequences">
          <h2>8. Consequences</h2>
          <p>Violations result in escalating consequences:</p>

          <table class="legal-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Level</th>
                <th>Violation Type</th>
                <th>Consequence</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Warning</td>
                <td>Minor first-time violations</td>
                <td>Content removed, educational message sent</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Timeout</td>
                <td>Repeated minor violations</td>
                <td>24-72 hour restriction from posting/battles</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Suspension</td>
                <td>Serious violations</td>
                <td>7-30 day account suspension</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Permanent Ban</td>
                <td>Severe or repeated serious violations</td>
                <td>Permanent platform ban, NFTs may be flagged</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h3>Immediate Permanent Ban</h3>
            <p>
              Some violations result in immediate permanent ban without warning:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>CSAM or child exploitation content</li>
              <li>Credible threats of violence</li>
              <li>Doxxing that endangers someone's safety</li>
              <li>Major scams resulting in financial harm</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="appeals">
          <h2>9. Appeals Process</h2>
          <p>
            We believe in fair process. If you believe a moderation action was wrong:
          </p>

          <h3>9.1 How to Appeal</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Wait 24 hours (cooling off period)</li>
            <li>Email <a href="mailto:appeals@worldbridger.one">appeals@worldbridger.one</a> with:
              <ul>
                <li>Your username/wallet address</li>
                <li>Date and description of the action</li>
                <li>Why you believe it was incorrect</li>
                <li>Any relevant context</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Allow 7 days for review</li>
          </ol>

          <h3>9.2 Appeal Review</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Appeals are reviewed by a different moderator than the original decision</li>
            <li>We consider all evidence and context</li>
            <li>Decisions are final after appeal review</li>
            <li>Frivolous appeals may result in appeal privileges being restricted</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="community-values">
          <h2>10. Community Values</h2>
          <p>
            Beyond rules, these are the values we aspire to as a community:
          </p>

          <div class="values-grid">
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Authenticity</h3>
              <p>Be real. Your unique voice matters more than copying trends.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Growth Mindset</h3>
              <p>Every L is a lesson. Use feedback to level up your craft.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Generosity</h3>
              <p>Share knowledge. The best artists lift others as they rise.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Resilience</h3>
              <p>Keep creating. Rejection and criticism are part of the journey.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Innovation</h3>
              <p>Push boundaries. Experiment with new sounds and styles.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Community</h3>
              <p>We're stronger together. Collaborate, compete, and connect.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>The WorldBridger One Promise</h3>
            <p>
              We're building more than a platform—we're building a movement.
              A space where young artists from Kakuma to Brooklyn can compete,
              learn, and earn. Where open source meets open mics. Where your
              talent matters more than your location or background.
            </p>
            <p>
              These guidelines exist to protect that vision. Follow them,
              and help us build something legendary.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

      </article>

      <footer class="legal-footer">
        <p>
          These Community Guidelines are licensed under
          <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>.
          Feel free to adapt them for your own projects.
        </p>
        <div class="legal-nav">
          <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
          <a href="/license">Open Source License</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
